<h2>Who is behind this thing?</h2>

<p>This site is developed by <a href="http://tourb.us/fan/mike">Mike Champion</a> and <a href="http://tourb.us/fan/gary">Gary Elliott</a>. 
Just two guys who like music and hacking.

<h2>Can I wear tourb.us?</h2>

<p>How could you <em>wear</em> a website? That doesn't even make sense. But we did make up a couple
<a href="http://www.cafepress.com/tourbus.47282567">t-shirts</a> and <a href="http://www.cafepress.com/tourbus.47355641">stickers</a> over at 
our <a href="http://www.cafepress.com/tourbus">CafePress store</a>. Check them out.

<h2>Respecting Your Privacy</h2>

<p>We will only use email addresses for password retrieval and sending show reminders which can
be stopped at any time (from the Settings page). We will never share your email address without
your prior approval. Any data we collect will never be used to identify you.

<h2>Removing your site from the tourb.us index</h2>

<p>As part of gathering a list of upcoming shows we crawl sites on a semi-frequent basis.
Like other web crawlers, we follow the <a href="http://www.robotstxt.org/wc/exclusion.html">robots.txt rules</a>
 and our crawler will specifically look for rules that apply to 'tourbusbot'. If you wish to prevent
your site from being crawled, add a snippet like this to your robots.txt: 
<br/><br/><code>
User-agent: tourbusbot<br/>
Disallow: /
</code>
</p>

<h2>What is tourb.us written in?</h2>

<p>Nerds that we are, we have to include that we've had a blast building tourb.us using 
<a href="http://rubyonrails.org/">Ruby on Rails</a>. The site is running on <a href="http://lighttpd.org/">Lighttpd</a> 
and hosted by the good (and very responsive) people over at <a href="http://www.liquidweb.com/">LiquidWeb</a>. If
this sort of thing interests you, check our <a href="http://blog.tourb.us">weblog</a> which details 
what's going on behind the scenes.
</p>

